<D>__{this way.}
<A>__{they move into a moonlit courtyard of the monastery. a hooded jesuit standing guard steps from the shadows, then recognizes aramis and admits the trio to the monastery's forge, where more hooded jesuits are working in secret, heating iron red hot in the bellows furnace.}
<C>__{athos}
<D>__{what are they doing?}
<C>__{aramis}
<D>__{making the key to the throne.}
<C>__{porthos}
<D>__{they are very large keys.}
<A>__{one of the blacksmiths uses tongs to remove something red from the fire; he hammers it in a shower of sparks and plunges it into water. aramis pulls the result from the water and shows it to athos and porthos. it is an iron mask.}
